==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from {{suffix|road|ster|lang=en}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a sea-going vessel [[ride|riding]] at anchor in a road or bay.
# {{label|en|nautical}} A clumsy vessel that works its way from one anchorage to another by means of the tides.
#: {{rfquotek|Ham. Nav. Encyc}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} A [[horse]] for riding on the road.
#* William Thackeray
#*: a sound, swift, well-fed hunter and '''roadster'''
# A bicycle, or tricycle, adapted for common roads, rather than for the racing track, usually of classic style & steel-framed.
# {{label|en|UK|dated}} One who drives much; a coach driver.
# {{label|en|UK|dated|slang}} A [[hunter]] who keeps to the [[road]]s instead of following the hounds across country.
# An open automobile having a front seat and a [[rumble seat]].
# A person who lives along the road.

